      "response": "\n\nImpressionism emerged in 1860s France as a radical departure from academic painting, emphasizing light and color primacy, broken color technique, visible brushwork, en plein air painting, and modern life subjects like cafes and railways. Named after Monet's \"Impression, Sunrise\" (1872), initially a derogatory term, it was influenced by photography, Japanese prints, and scientific color theory, while facing Salon rejection for its \"unfinished\" appearance. Its legacy liberated color from mere description and emphasized perception over representation, paving the way for Post-Impressionism, Fauvism, and Abstract art.",
